by cakeisnotpie

Strangely enough, that’s the beginning of a long road that just might lead to happiness for himself and one Phil Coulson, the man he’s been pining over for a long time. title: iron dad bingo
body:
Bingos have been around fandoms for a while and I was surprised that this group hadn’t had anyone running one, so I thought I’d try my hand at trying to put something together. 

Right now, I’m taking suggestions on what to offer on the cards, so it would mean the world if you could click this form and fill it out with some ideas. For ex: tropes, dialogues, aus, whump, and all that fun stuff. Any kind of prompt you think would be good on an Iron Dad bingo card!

Once I start collecting a god amount of ideas, I’ll open up the actual form to receive a board!

summary: A scene I want to see in a future Avengers movie
body:
A scene I want to see in a future Avengers movie

Thor: Friend Stark, please sit down. We have much to discuss with you.

Tony: Didn’t know Malibu Ken was calling meetings now but whatever.

Cap: Thor didnt call this meeting, Tony. I did.

Tony: Yes, I know. You’re Malibu Ken. What’s up?

Widow: You’re a sexist jackass.

Tony: I thought we were meeting about something new?

Widow: Why the hell do Cap and Hawkeye make more money than me?

Tony: *flustered* I-uh-I dont know what you mean?

Vision: Miss Romanov’s yearly income is $300,000, where as Mr. Barton’s is $450,000.

Wanda: She makes three hundred thousand! You only pay me one hundred!

Clint: Everyone say how much money you make, now!

Tony: Whoever doesnt speak gets their wage doubled!

*everyone except Peter shouts a number*

Cap: Come on son, be a team player.

Peter: …You guys are getting paid????

Rhodey: REALLY, TONY, REALLY?!

body:
Marvel Snippet Monday

Trying to update my update schedule, and keep myself working on all my fandoms. So, Marvel Monday, Gundam Wing Wednesday, and VLD Friday or Saturday. Anywho, here’s a thing for @kangofu-cb . It’s crack, but y'all can deal. (Also, as I’m shit at naming wips, this file is literally called…)

•°●°•

He’s been waiting for this for weeks. So long, in fact, that when Steven Grant Rogers goes into a tailspin, Tony almost misses it because it’s over something so small.

“But, Tony, what if it burns?”

“It’s not gonna burn, Cap.”

“When do you flip it?”

“Flip-? What? You don’t flip it.”

“Do you have to watch it? Won’t it get all black and shi-”

And it’s the cause of the meltdown that’s so shocking. It’s not over any of the shiny new StarkTech. It’s not over some new building, or enemy. Not some scientific discovery or mystical bullshit. Not some stupid meme that Barton is shoving down their throat this week.

Captain America…

“It really does both sides?”

… is having an existential crisis…

“Yes, Steve, and we’re running out of bread.”

… over the god-damned toaster.

summary: On All Levels, I Am A Spider
title: On All Levels, I Am A Spider
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2UJIotw

by Yousaydoctorisaywho

Peter nodded and grabbed a piece, not looking at the label. He popped it in his mouth and the minute he bite down, a look of pure horror and disgust washed over his face. His mouth opened and the blue, peppermint flavored gum dropped out of his mouth, falling to the ground with a wet plop.
Tony wrinkled his nose in disgust and stepped back. “Yech, kid that was so gross-“
“What the hell was that.” Peter whispered mainly to himself, staring at the gum on the floor.

summary: okay, but Peter “when you can the things that I can but you don’t and the bad things happen, they happen because of you” Parker...
body: okay, but Peter “when you can the things that I can but you don’t and the bad things happen, they happen because of you” Parker died in Tony Stark’s arms. So, what if he comes back after from, presumably, the soul stone only to find out Tony died saving him and everyone else with the rest of the Avengers. I mean, this kid holds this “moral obligation” to always save people and protect everyone he can but then his mentor/third father figure dies while he’s dead because he couldn’t help enough to defeat Thanos. This child comes back from the dead just thinking that had he been strong enough, he would have been there to stop the bad thing from happening and maybe he could have helped and Tony wouldn’t be dead.
